				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-462616/scp-1209#post-3041314</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sat, 01 Jul 2017 13:59:50 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>Rioghail</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1302192</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I hold the opinion that, since SCP-1209 is a congenital malformation rather than an infectious disease, SCP-1209-1 represent a fully-fledged component of the anomaly rather than a non-anomalous 'host', and so should be included in tagging - sapient and humanoid refer to them.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
